Analysis of the Main Target Image  
•  Overall there are two separate “mini‐structures.”  
  – Left “Tower”:  
    1.  Bottom layer is a red arch block.  
    2.  Above it is a horizontally‐placed green rectangular block.  
    3.  Above that is a blue cube.  
    4.  Capping the cube is an orange wedge (roof shape).  
    5.  Next to the arch tower is a vertical orange cylinder with another orange wedge on top.  
  – Right “Vehicle”:  
    1.  Two horizontally‐lying orange cylinders form the “wheels.”  
    2.  A horizontal yellow rectangular block rests across the two cylinders.  
    3.  A blue cube sits on top of the yellow block (as the “cab”).  

•  Block Count and Layers:  
  – The left tower effectively has four layers (arch → green block → cube → roof), plus an adjacent cylinder‐plus‐roof.  
  – The right vehicle has two layers of wheels, then a yellow block, then a blue cube.  

Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary  
•  Matching Each Piece Exactly (no re‐orientations allowed):  
  1.  Red arch at the tower base → Dictionary index 1  
  2.  Green rectangular block (horizontal) → Dictionary index 5  
  3.  Blue cube (used twice: tower and vehicle) → Dictionary index 3 (×2)  
  4.  Orange wedge/roof (front‐to‐back orientation) → Dictionary index 15 (×2)  
  5.  Vertical orange cylinder → Dictionary index 9  
  6.  Two orange cylinders lying horizontally (vehicle wheels) → Dictionary index 10 (×2)  
  7.  Yellow rectangular block (horizontal) → Dictionary index 7  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 5  
  Step3: Move block with index 3  
  Step4: Move block with index 15  
  Step5: Move block with index 9  
  Step6: Move block with index 15  
  Step7: Move block with index 10  
  Step8: Move block with index 10  
  Step9: Move block with index 7  
  Step10: Move block with index 3  
}
